This paper deals with the performance analysis of wireless networks with full-duplex multi-antenna base stations and half-duplex user equipments. The paper focuses on the spectral efficiency and interference cancellation, which are key topics in the field of network information theory (cs.IT) and network optimization (cs.SY). The use of multi-antenna BSs/UEs also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM) as MIMO technology is often used in multimedia applications. Finally, the paper provides design guidelines for the practical implementation of FD technology in large small-cell networks, which falls under the sub-category of computer networks and communications (cs.COM). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) as the paper deals with the performance analysis of wireless networks.
